sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: COX3 termi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Terminator of Yeast mitochondrial gene COX3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the terminator region for COX3 gene. It is selected from Yeast mito-chromosome, and we want to test it in our experiment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We modelled the RNA secondary structure of COX3 3'UTR region, and found that the secondary structure of this region is very similar to bacterial terminator sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is obtained from Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C mito-chromosome region. http://www.yeastgenome.org/

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mt ori7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Qiwu XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ori 7 region of Saccharomyces cerevisiae mtDNA, works as replication initial site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NCBI database of Saccharomyces cerevisiae's genome

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809504
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick is to produce GFP with the control of REX binding on ROP site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All parts should be correctly linked without frame shift and Restriction Enzyme cutting site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P+ROP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is regulatory sequence which can be repressed by binding of REX on ROP site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: With different place of ROP and promoter, the effect of REX binding on ROP might differs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: 1. Brekasis, D. and M. S. Paget (2003). "A novel sensor of NADH/NAD+ redox poise in Streptomyces coelicolor A3(2)." EMBO J 22(18): 4856-4865. 2. Deshpande, A. P. and S. S. Patel (2012). "Mechanism of transcription initiation by the yeast mitochondrial RNA polymerase." Biochim Biophys Acta.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809106
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick is used to test the efficient of COX3 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The biobrick should be usable and all the biobricks won't interfere with each other.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ROP+P
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is regulatory sequence which can be repressed by binding of REX on ROP site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: With different place of ROP and promoter, the effect of REX binding on ROP might differs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: 1. Brekasis, D. and M. S. Paget (2003). "A novel sensor of NADH/NAD+ redox poise in Streptomyces coelicolor A3(2)." EMBO J 22(18): 4856-4865. 2. Deshpande, A. P. and S. S. Patel (2012). "Mechanism of transcription initiation by the yeast mitochondrial RNA polymerase." Biochim Biophys Acta. 3. http://regulondb.ccg.unam.mx/

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AI1 RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RBS sequence of yeast mitochondrial gene AI1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the RBS region for AI1 gene. It is selected from Yeast mito-chromosome, and we want to test it in our experiment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence between the last ATG codon and CDS on the 3'UTR DNA sequence is believed to contain RBS. With some modifications, we made those sequences BioBricks.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is obtained from Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C mito-chromosome region. http://www.yeastgenome.org/

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick is to produce GFP with the control of REX binding on ROP site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All parts should be correctly linked without frame shift and Restriction Enzyme cutting site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Senwei TANG, Qiwu XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Mitochondrial expression vector, with initial site ori7, up elements of cox2 gene (including promoter and RBS), and mtGFP.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: UPcox1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Qiwu XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Up elements (including promoter and RBS) of cox2 gene from Saccharomyces cerevisiae mitochondrial DNA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Designed by Qiwu XU, BioBrick restriction enzyme sites added.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SP_REX
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: REX is tagged with signal peptide of ZIM17, thus can be targetted into mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part BBa_K809201 and BBa_K809401 should be correctly linked without frame shift

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: COX1 promo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter of Yeast mitochondrial gene COX1/Oli1/15s rRNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiaopeng Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence is synthesized based on the sequences retrived.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Deshpande, A. P. and S. S. Patel (2012). "Mechanism of transcription initiation by the yeast mitochondrial RNA polymerase." Biochim Biophys Acta.
